   <text>
      <body>
         <pb n="136"/>
         <milestone n="136" unit="page"/>
         <lb/>
         <lb/>
         <lg n="1" type="stanza">
            <l n="1">Three years she grew in sun and shower,</l>
            <l n="2">Then Nature said, “A lovelier flower</l>
            <l n="3">On earth was never sown;</l>
            <l n="4">This Child I to myself will take<del>,</del>
               <add place="rmargin" resp="ww">;/</add>
            </l>
            <l n="5">She shall be mine, and I will make</l>
            <l n="6">A Lady of my own.</l>
         </lg>
         <lg n="2" type="stanza">
            <l n="7" rend="ms.">
               <add hand="dw" resp="ww">Her teacher I myself will
                                        be,</add>
            </l>
            <l n="7">
               <del>Myself will to my darling be</del>
            </l>
            <l n="8">
               <add place="lmargin" resp="ww">/;</add>
               <del>Both law and impulse</del>
               <del>,</del>
               <add place="belowline" resp="ww">^</add>
               <add hand="dw" place="aboveline" resp="ww">She is my darling;—</add>and with me</l>
            <l n="9">
               <add place="rmargin" resp="ww">/,</add> The Girl<add place="belowline" resp="ww">^</add>in rock and plain,</l>
            <l n="10">In earth and heaven, in glade and bower,</l>
            <l n="11">Shall feel an overseeing power</l>
            <l n="12">To kindle or restrain.</l>
         </lg>
         <pb n="137"/>
         <milestone n="137" unit="page"/>
         <lb/>
         <lb/>
         <lg n="3" type="stanza">
            <l n="13">She shall be sportive as the <del>f</del>awn <add place="rmargin" resp="ww">F/</add>
            </l>
            <l n="14">That wild with glee across the lawn</l>
            <l n="15">Or up the mountain springs<del>,</del>
               <add place="rmargin" resp="ww">;/</add>
            </l>
            <l n="16">And hers shall be the breathing balm,</l>
            <l n="17">And hers the silence and the calm</l>
            <l n="18">Of mute insensate things.</l>
         </lg>
         <lg n="4" type="stanza">
            <l n="19">
               <add place="lmargin" resp="ww">/C</add> The floating
                                        <del>c</del>louds their state shall lend</l>
            <l n="20">
               <add place="lmargin" resp="ww">/;</add> To
                                        her<del>,</del> for her the willow bend<del>,</del>
               <add place="rmargin" resp="ww">;/</add>
            </l>
            <l n="21">Nor shall she fail to see</l>
            <l n="22">Even in the motions of the <del>s</del>torm <add place="rmargin" resp="ww">S/</add>
            </l>
            <l n="23" rend="ms.">
               <add hand="dw" place="aboveline" resp="ww">Grace
                                        that shall mould the Maiden’s form</add>
            </l>
            <l n="23">
               <del>A beauty that shall mould her form</del>
            </l>
            <l n="24">By silent sympathy.</l>
         </lg>
         <lg n="3" type="stanza">
            <l n="25">
               <add place="lmargin" resp="ww">SS</add> The <del>s</del>tars
                                   of midnight shall be dear</l>
            <l n="26">
               <add place="lmargin" resp="ww">;</add> To her<del>,</del>
                                   and she shall lean her ear</l>
            <l n="27">In many a secret place</l>
            <l n="28">
               <add place="lmargin" resp="ww">/R</add> Where
                                        <del>r</del>ivulets dance their wayward round,</l>
            <l n="29">And beauty born of murmuring sound</l>
            <l n="30">Shall pass into her face.</l>
         </lg>
         <pb n="138"/>
         <milestone unit="page" n="138"/>
         <lb/>
         <lb/>
         <lg n="6" type="stanza">
            <l n="31">And vital feelings of delight</l>
            <l n="32">Shall rear her form to stately height,</l>
            <l n="33">Her virgin bosom swell<del>,</del>
               <add place="rmargin" resp="ww">;/</add>
            </l>
            <l n="34">Such thoughts to Lucy I will give</l>
            <l n="35">While she and I together live</l>
            <l n="36">Here in this happy <del>d</del>ell. ”<add place="belowline" resp="ww">^/</add>
               <add place="rmargin" resp="ww">D/</add>
            </l>
         </lg>
         <lg n="7" type="stanza">
            <l n="37">Thus Nature spake—The work was done—</l>
            <l n="38">How soon my Lucy’s race was run!</l>
            <l n="39">She died and left to me</l>
            <l n="40">This heath, this calm and quiet scene<del>,</del>
               <add place="rmargin" resp="ww">;/</add>
            </l>
            <l n="41">The memory of what has been,</l>
            <l n="42">And never more will be.</l>
         </lg>
      </body>
   </text>
